我不知道。

193
00:19:12,193 --> 00:19:13,486
Does he have X-ray vision?
他有X光视力吗？

194
00:19:13,737 --> 00:19:15,780
If he has X-ray vision, we can't send him to school.
如果他有X光视力，我们就不能送他去学校。

195
00:19:15,864 --> 00:19:16,882
You know that, right?
你知道的，对吧？

196
00:19:16,906 --> 00:19:18,533
I think it's just the heat vision.
我认为这只是火热的视觉。

197
00:19:18,616 --> 00:19:21,578
You think? We need to know, Clark, this is serious.
你是这么想的吗？我们需要知道，克拉克，这是严肃的。

198
00:19:21,661 --> 00:19:23,663
So that means that I'm a superhero, too, right?
所以这意味着我也是一个超级英雄，对吗？

199
00:19:23,747 --> 00:19:26,787
Like, does that... does that mean I get to join the justice league and stuff?
就像，那是不是...这是不是意味着我可以加入正义联盟之类的组织？

200
00:19:27,208 --> 00:19:28,752
Do I get to meet Batman?
我能见见蝙蝠侠吗？

201
00:19:29,419 --> 00:19:30,587
What are we gonna do?
我们该怎么办？

202
00:19:31,713 --> 00:19:33,757
We knew this was a possibility. I just...
我们知道这是一种可能性。我只是.。

203
00:19:33,840 --> 00:19:36,301
He wasn't lifting cars at two years old like you were.
他在两岁的时候不会像你那样举起汽车。

204
00:19:36,384 --> 00:19:40,263
So, I thought maybe it skipped a generation, like, red hair.
所以，我想它可能跳过了一代人，比如，红发。

205
00:19:40,347 --> 00:19:43,350
Don't worry, I'll get him checked out. We'll see what's happening.
别担心，我会给他做检查的。我们看看会发生什么。

206
00:19:44,225 --> 00:19:45,225
It'll be fine.
一切都会好的。

207
00:19:50,982 --> 00:19:52,442
Nope. Can't fly.
不是的。不会飞。

208
00:19:53,777 --> 00:19:54,778
Mostly fine.
基本没问题。

209
00:19:57,072 --> 00:19:59,532
Woo-hoo!
哇-呼！

210
00:19:59,783 --> 00:20:01,076
Yeah!
嗯!

211
00:20:10,794 --> 00:20:12,420
Woo-hoo!
哇-呼！

212
00:20:12,754 --> 00:20:14,047
Oh, yeah!
哦，耶！

213
00:20:47,122 --> 00:20:48,206
Whoa.
哇哦。

214
00:20:52,836 --> 00:20:53,836
Yeah!
嗯!

215
00:20:55,922 --> 00:20:58,049
Woo-hoo!
哇-呼！

216
00:21:11,646 --> 00:21:13,064
Mom? Mom!
妈妈?妈妈!

217
00:21:14,149 --> 00:21:15,316
What, honey?
怎么了，亲爱的？

218
00:21:16,276 --> 00:21:19,446
Superman is out the window and he has some kid hanging on his back.
超人就在窗外，背上挂着几个孩子。

219
00:21:26,035 --> 00:21:29,247
Yeah, you know what? I was wrong.
是啊，你知道吗？我错了。

220
00:21:29,581 --> 00:21:31,541
Here's my phone. Have some fun.
这是我的手机。玩得开心点。

221
00:21:38,339 --> 00:21:40,508
This is amazing!
这真是太棒了！

222
00:21:41,092 --> 00:21:42,927
My favorite part of being an alien.
作为一个外星人我最喜欢的部分。

223
00:21:43,970 --> 00:21:45,930
So, you're... okay. So...
所以，你是..。好吧。所以..。

224
00:21:47,432 --> 00:21:49,392
That means that I'm half alien, too, right?
这意味着我也是半个外星人，对吗？

225
00:21:49,476 --> 00:21:50,476
I'm half alien.
我是半个外星人。

226
00:21:51,019 --> 00:21:52,145
I'm half alien!
我是半个外星人！

227
00:21:53,396 --> 00:21:54,856
I'm half alien!
我是半个外星人！

228
00:21:56,024 --> 00:21:58,276
You're taking this a lot better than I thought you would.
你接受这件事比我想象的要好得多。

229
00:21:59,319 --> 00:22:01,779
Why wouldn't I? I mean, this...
我怎么会不想呢？我是说，这..。

230
00:22:01,863 --> 00:22:05,950
My dad is the greatest superhero in the world.
我爸爸是世界上最伟大的超级英雄。

231
00:22:06,451 --> 00:22:07,452
Besides Batman.
除了蝙蝠侠。

232
00:22:07,535 --> 00:22:10,205
It's pretty much the greatest birthday present ever.
这几乎是有史以来最棒的生日礼物了。

233
00:22:10,288 --> 00:22:12,957
Yeah. It's been really hard not to tell you,
嗯。很难不告诉你，

234
00:22:13,041 --> 00:22:16,419
but keeping you and your mother safe is my top priority.
但保护你和你母亲的安全是我的首要任务。

235
00:22:17,128 --> 00:22:19,005
That means being on call.
这意味着随时待命。

236
00:22:20,131 --> 00:22:22,842
My job, my real job is helping the world.
我的工作，我真正的工作是帮助世界。

237
00:22:23,092 --> 00:22:25,803
Standing for truth, justice and the American way,
代表真理、正义和美国方式，

238
00:22:26,054 --> 00:22:27,263
wherever that takes me.
无论它带我去哪里。

239
00:22:27,597 --> 00:22:28,681
Awesome.
太棒了。

240
00:22:29,224 --> 00:22:32,769
Sometimes. But as glamorous as you might think this is,
有时候。但是，尽管你可能认为这很迷人，

241
00:22:33,561 --> 00:22:35,355
it takes me away from you and your mother.
这会让我远离你和你母亲。

242
00:22:35,813 --> 00:22:38,107
And you should know it's dangerous.
你应该知道这很危险。

243
00:22:38,858 --> 00:22:40,109
It's a real sacrifice.
这是一次真正的牺牲。

244
00:22:40,860 --> 00:22:41,778
Uh-huh, uh-huh.
嗯，嗯，嗯。

245
00:22:41,861 --> 00:22:43,488
Oh, what should I be called though?
哦，那我该叫什么呢？

246
00:22:43,696 --> 00:22:46,115
What about... what about... Well, superboy's taken, right?
那..。那..。嗯，超人已经有人了，对吧？

247
00:22:46,199 --> 00:22:51,120
So, what about, uh, dragoneyes, but with a "," z or supremo?
那么，那么，呃，龙眼，但有一个“，”z或最高领导人？

248
00:22:51,412 --> 00:22:54,082
Or, uh, kid wonder!
或者，呃，小魔童！

249
00:22:54,541 --> 00:22:58,044
Superman two or... Ugh! What's that smell?
超人2或..。啊！这是什么味儿？

250
00:22:58,586 --> 00:22:59,754
Gotham city.
哥谭市。

251
00:23:04,008 --> 00:23:05,260
This is Gotham?
这就是哥谭市？

252
00:23:05,885 --> 00:23:07,595
I thought the Internet was exaggerating.
我觉得互联网太夸张了。

253
00:23:07,679 --> 00:23:10,890
But why doesn't somebody do something about this?
但为什么没有人对此做点什么呢？

254
00:23:11,266 --> 00:23:12,267
Somebody is.
有人是这样的。

255
00:23:24,737 --> 00:23:25,737
Get him!
抓住他！

256
00:23:32,287 --> 00:23:35,832
- Uh, dad, shouldn't we help him? - No.
-爸爸，我们不该帮他吗？-不.

257
00:23:36,332 --> 00:23:38,960
He tends to get a bit grumpy when I step in.
当我插手时，他往往会变得有点暴躁。

258
00:23:41,754 --> 00:23:44,007
Is he always this... oh!
他总是这么..。噢!

259
00:23:44,090 --> 00:23:46,509
Rough? It's not as bad as it looks.
粗暴？情况并不像看起来那么糟糕。

260
00:23:47,051 --> 00:23:48,803
He's actually going pretty easy on them.
实际上，他对他们的态度相当宽松。

261
00:23:52,932 --> 00:23:53,933
That's easy?
这很容易吗？

262
00:23:54,100 --> 00:23:56,352
This is my town, Batman.
这是我的小镇，蝙蝠侠。

263
00:24:01,733 --> 00:24:02,733
Hey.
嘿。

264
00:24:11,200 --> 00:24:12,410
Aw...
啊..。

265
00:24:12,493 --> 00:24:15,663
Come on, Batman. Let's come to an agreement, huh?
来吧，蝙蝠侠。让我们达成协议，好吗？

266
00:24:15,747 --> 00:24:20,084
I'll promise to be a good bird and you let me fly the Coop, eh?
我保证做一只好鸟，你让我飞，好吗？

267
00:24:22,503 --> 00:24:23,546
Okay.
好吧。

268
00:24:24,672 --> 00:24:25,965
No way!
不行!

269
00:24:36,059 --> 00:24:37,060
Clark.
克拉克。

270
00:24:41,606 --> 00:24:43,524
Hey, a little help here?
嘿，帮个忙好吗？

271
00:24:45,526 --> 00:24:47,278
You... you... you're...
你.。你.。你是..。

272
00:24:47,403 --> 00:24:48,529
I'm Batman.
我是蝙蝠侠。

273
00:24:49,530 --> 00:24:50,530
Wow!
哇!

274
00:24:56,913 --> 00:24:59,123
This is the... wow!
这是..。哇!

275
00:24:59,248 --> 00:25:01,876
- This is the... - Welcome to the batcave.
-这是...-欢迎来到蝙蝠洞。

276
00:25:12,136 --> 00:25:14,097
Look! That's the Batmobile,
看!那是蝙蝠车，

277
00:25:14,972 --> 00:25:16,099
and the batcomputer,
和蝙蝠计算机，

278
00:25:16,432 --> 00:25:18,017
and the batdinosaur. And that...
还有蝙蝠龙。而那..。

279
00:25:18,101 --> 00:25:20,061
Who's the new kid? Obvious boy?
新来的孩子是谁？显而易见的男孩？

280
00:25:24,440 --> 00:25:27,110
Jon, this is Batman's son, Damian.
乔恩，这是蝙蝠侠的儿子达米安。

281
00:25:27,193 --> 00:25:28,193
Jon?
琼恩?

282
00:25:28,486 --> 00:25:30,530
So, you have toilet powers?
所以，你有厕所的力量？

283
00:25:31,698 --> 00:25:33,741
Relax, Damian. They're friends.
放松点，达米安。他们是朋友。

284
00:25:33,991 --> 00:25:36,119
Sure. Friends.
好的。朋友。

285
00:25:36,661 --> 00:25:40,915
So should I go into your utility belt and get the you-know-what-a-nite?
那我是不是应该到你的实用腰带里去买个你知道的夜宵？

286
00:25:40,998 --> 00:25:43,209
Damian, please. They need our help.
达米安，拜托。他们需要我们的帮助。

287
00:25:43,334 --> 00:25:44,919
Set up Jon in the meta analyzer.
在元分析器中设置Jon。

288
00:25:45,211 --> 00:25:48,840
Don't you mean the bat meta analyzer?
你是说BAT元分析器吗？

289
00:25:50,341 --> 00:25:52,885
Sorry. Sorry. I just thought... Never mind.
抱歉的。抱歉的。我只是想..。不要紧。

290
00:25:53,302 --> 00:25:56,055
Fine. Follow me, farm boy.
很好。跟我来，农场男孩。

291
00:25:56,848 --> 00:25:59,809
- Is that a giant penny? - Don't touch the penny.
-那是一个巨大的便士吗？-别碰那个便士.

292
00:26:00,143 --> 00:26:01,519
In fact, don't touch anything.
事实上，什么都不要碰。

293
00:26:08,401 --> 00:26:11,279
- Reminds me of us when we first met. - I was nicer.
-让我想起了我们第一次见面的时候。-我更友善。

294
00:26:12,029 --> 00:26:13,030
How's he doing?
他怎么样了？

295
00:26:13,239 --> 00:26:15,074
I mean, now that he's living with you.
我是说，现在他和你住在一起。

296
00:26:15,533 --> 00:26:17,827
He wants to be good, I think.
我想，他想做个好人。

297
00:26:18,202 --> 00:26:20,163
But what ra's and Talia put him through...
但是Ra和Talia让他经历的..。

298
00:26:20,955 --> 00:26:21,956
Give it time.
给它点时间。

299
00:26:22,415 --> 00:26:24,250
No one ever said parenting would be easy.
从来没有人说养育孩子是一件容易的事。

300
00:26:24,917 --> 00:26:26,753
Especially when they've been through so much.
尤其是他们经历了这么多。

301
00:26:27,253 --> 00:26:28,880
Thanks. I hope so.
谢谢。要是那样就好了。

302
00:26:39,932 --> 00:26:41,309
- He's done. - Well?
-他完蛋了.-怎么了？

303
00:26:41,893 --> 00:26:43,060
Nothing definitive.
没什么确定的。

304
00:26:43,269 --> 00:26:47,356
I have no idea what powers could manifest next, if any at all.
我不知道下一步会有什么能力，如果真的有的话。

305
00:26:47,982 --> 00:26:50,693
If his first power set was brought on by extreme stress,
如果他的第一套动力装置是由极端的压力引起的，

306
00:26:50,777 --> 00:26:51,819
it stands to reason
言之有礼

307
00:26:51,903 --> 00:26:53,213
that another traumatic moment...
又一个创伤性的时刻。

308
00:26:53,237 --> 00:26:54,781
Might unlock something else.
可能会解锁其他东西。

309
00:26:55,198 --> 00:26:56,491
Let's test that theory.
让我们来检验一下这一理论。

310
00:26:59,410 --> 00:27:00,410
Damian!
达米安！

311
00:27:17,303 --> 00:27:19,430
What was that? Are you kidding me?
那是什么？你在开我的玩笑吗？

312
00:27:19,639 --> 00:27:21,224
- You piece of... - What?
-你这个……-什么？

313
00:27:21,766 --> 00:27:24,685
You said a traumatic moment might help him unlock some more powers.
你说过创伤性的时刻可能会帮助他释放更多的力量。

314
00:27:24,769 --> 00:27:25,937
Seems logical to test it out.
测试一下似乎是合乎逻辑的。

315
00:27:26,395 --> 00:27:27,939
Not by trying to kill him.
而不是试图杀了他。

316
00:27:28,856 --> 00:27:31,442
If I wanted to do that, he'd already be dead.
如果我想这么做，他早就死了。

317
00:27:31,526 --> 00:27:32,401
That's enough.
足够了。

318
00:27:32,527 --> 00:27:33,569
Who is this kid?
这孩子是谁？

319
00:27:35,613 --> 00:27:37,114
Out. Now!
出去。现在!

320
00:27:37,281 --> 00:27:38,950
Well, he's obviously not invulnerable.
他显然不是无懈可击的。

321
00:27:39,784 --> 00:27:41,285
Obviously.
很明显。

322
00:27:43,329 --> 00:27:44,330
I'm sorry.
对不起。

323
00:27:44,455 --> 00:27:46,499
It's okay. He's had a tough time.
没关系的。他经历了一段艰难的时期。

324
00:27:46,791 --> 00:27:48,584
He's had a tough time?
他经历了一段艰难的时光？

325
00:27:49,669 --> 00:27:51,921
Jonathan, could I borrow your dad for a minute?
乔纳森，我能借你爸爸用一下吗？

326
00:27:52,088 --> 00:27:54,090
Yeah. Oh, yeah, of course. Sure, sure, sure.
嗯。哦，是的，当然。当然，当然，当然。

327
00:27:54,340 --> 00:27:57,593
I'll just be over here, you know, nursing my bat wounds.
我就在这里，你知道，护理我的蝙蝠伤口。

328
00:27:58,344 --> 00:27:59,905
Have you heard from the watchtower lately?
你最近有瞭望塔的消息吗？

329
00:27:59,929 --> 00:28:01,430
Green arrow hasn't checked in?
绿箭公司还没入住吗？

330
00:28:01,514 --> 00:28:03,354
He said he'd give you updates after last night.
他说昨晚过后他会给你最新消息。

331
00:28:03,766 --> 00:28:04,684
Last night?
昨晚?

332
00:28:04,767 --> 00:28:07,103
